players.name: Ernan Siluane
players.summary: Ernan Alberto Siluane, sometimes known as Ernani, is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Black Bulls and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Ivane Urrubal
players.summary: Ivane Carminio Francisco Oficial Urrubal is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a goalkeeper for Songo and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Nanani
players.summary: Infren da Conceição David Matola, known as Nanani, is a Mozambican footballer who plays as a defender for Liga Desportiva de Maputo and the Mozambique national football team.

players.name: Bruno Langa
players.summary: Bruno Alberto Langa is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a left-back for Cypriot club Pafos FC, on loan from Spanish club UD Almería, and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Edmilson Dove
players.summary: Edmilson Gabriel Dove is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays for Mozambique national team. He primarily plays as a defender, but has also played as a midfielder.

players.name: Reinildo Mandava
players.summary: Reinildo Isnard Mandava, also known mononymously as Reinildo, is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a left-back for Premier League club Sunderland and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Mexer
players.summary: Edson André Sitoe, known as Mexer, is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for TFF 1. Lig club Ankara Keçiörengücü and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Diogo Calila
players.summary: Diogo dos Santos Cabral, known as Diogo Calila, is a professional footballer who plays as a right-back for Primeira Liga club Santa Clara and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Manuel Kambala
players.summary: Manuel Nhanga Kambala is a Mozambican footballer who plays as a midfielder for Polokwane City. South African football fans nicknamed him "THE LORD KAMBALA" for what he did in 2019/20 season in PSL, scoring an equalising goal in the last game of the season against Kaizer Chiefs, denying them the league.

players.name: Domingues
players.summary: Elias Gaspar Pelembe, also known simply as Domingues, is a Mozambican footballer who plays for UD Songo and Mozambique. His position is midfielder.

players.name: Geny Catamo
players.summary: Geny Cipriano Catamo is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a winger or wing-back for Primeira Liga club Sporting CP and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: João Bonde
players.summary: João José Jone Bonde, sometimes known as Maza, is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Ferroviário Beira and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Alfons Amade
players.summary: Alfons Antonio Chico Amade is a professional footballer who plays as a right-back for Dunfermline Athletic. Born in Germany, he represents the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Guima
players.summary:
Guima is a nick name, short for Guimarães. It may refer to:Guima, Bruno Guimarães Pinho de Azevedo, Portuguese football striker
Guima, Ricardo Martins Guimarães, Mozambican football midfielder for Chaves

players.name: Shaquille
players.summary: Shaquille Rashaun O'Neal, commonly known as Shaq, is an American former professional basketball player who is a sports analyst on the television program Inside the NBA. He is a 7-foot-1-inch (2.16 m) and 325-pound (147 kg) center who played for six teams over his 19-year career in the National Basketball Association (NBA) and is a four-time NBA champion. O'Neal is widely regarded as one of the greatest basketball players and centers of all time.

players.name: Faisal Bangal
players.summary: Faisal Bangal is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a forward for Serie D club Mestre.

players.name: Stanley Ratifo
players.summary: Stanley Ratifo is a professional footballer who plays as a forward for BSG Chemie Leipzig. Born in Germany, he plays for the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Gildo Vilanculos
players.summary: Gildo Lourenço Vilanculos is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a winger for Lebanese club Tadamon Sour and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Witi
players.summary: Witiness Chimoio João Quembo, known as Witi, is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a winger for Primeira Liga club Nacional and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Melque Alexandre
players.summary: Melque Melito Alexandre Garcia is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a forward for Moçambola club Songo and the Mozambique national team.

players.name: Chamito
players.summary: Chamito Loborino Alfândega, known as Chamito, is a Mozambican footballer who plays as a forward for Portuguese club Académico de Viseu.

players.name: Clésio
players.summary: Clésio Palmirim David Baúque, known simply as Clésio, is a Mozambican professional footballer who plays as a winger for Mozambican side Black Bulls and the Mozambique national team.
